It is probably a compiler/library bug, as little variant works:

- Being explicit about `initializer_list` ([Demo](https://gcc.godbolt.org/z/EqWca7)):

    ```
    std::set my_set(std::initializer_list&lt;Foo&gt;{Foo{}, Foo{}}, cmp);
    ```

- adding allocator ([Demo](https://wandbox.org/permlink/xTt6HHj30I0fVAkx)):

    ```
    std::set my_set({Foo{}, Foo{}}, cmp, std::allocator&lt;Foo&gt;{});
    ```

- using Functor ([Demo](https://gcc.godbolt.org/z/0-j6-6)):

    ```
    struct MyComparer
    {
        bool operator()(const Foo&amp;, const Foo&amp;) const;
    };

