answers.body_markdown:
You have to use the `or` keyword from sequelize like mention [in the documentation][1]

Example: 

```
const findNameTsxData = (limit: number, Names: string[]): Promise&lt;FinanceStuffs[]&gt; =&gt; {
const Op = Sequelize.Op;
  return db.FinanceStuffs.findAll({
    where: { Name: { [Op.or]: Names } },
    limit
  });
};
```

You can also use the `in` if you prefer

```
const findNameTsxData = (limit: number, Names: string[]): Promise&lt;FinanceStuffs[]&gt; =&gt; {
const Op = Sequelize.Op;
  return db.FinanceStuffs.findAll({
    where: { Name: { [Op.in]: Names } },
    limit
  });
};
```

  [1]: https://sequelize.org/master/manual/querying.html#where

